Ternary Conditional Operators can fuck right off. Code readability is much more important than packing everything into one line.Also, the example given:if a<b:  min = aelse:  min = bWill set off some "code smell" alarms and ask for this:min = bif a<b:  min = aOf course, this is a contrived example that would best be represented as min(a,b)Same goes for lambda functions... readability is important. Other than that, no notes.
Yes, I code all my functions as recursive lambdas, it's much more elegant.Wtf is this guide?
